President Trump and First Lady Melania Trump visited the Yokosuka Naval Base in Japan. The President thanked the sailors and Marines for their service and sacrifice. He also discussed the strong relationship between the US and Japan and the importance of the US military presence in the Pacific. He highlighted the investments made in the military and the new equipment being provided, including F-35B Marine fighter aircraft. The President also mentioned the debate between using steam or electric catapults on aircraft carriers, expressing his preference for steam. He honored the memory of fallen American soldiers on Memorial Day and thanked the military for their dedication and bravery.